@Endnode
@Node "STP" "Starting the program"

@{b}@{u}Starting the program@{uu}@{ub}

ScreenToIFF can be started from Workbench by double-clicking on its icon, or
from a Shell window by typing in its name (type in 'ScreenToIFF ?' to see the
complete CLI template).

See @{"ToolTypes" link "TOO"} and @{"CLI arguments" link "CLI"} for the program's settings.


@Endnode
@Node "TOO" "ToolTypes"

@{b}@{u}ToolTypes@{uu}@{ub}

ScreenToIFF recognizes the following ToolTypes:

   @{b}XPOS=<n>@{ub}
   Specifies the @{"main window" link "MAW"}'s horizontal position.

   @{b}YPOS=<n>@{ub}
   Specifies the @{"main window" link "MAW"}'s vertical position.

   @{b}PUBLIC@{ub}
   Indicates you want to handle public screens only.

   @{b}ASKFILENAME@{ub}
   Indicates you want a file requester to appear when saving the screens,
   otherwise, the program will save the screens in the directory specified by
   'DESTPATH' with the name of the screens themselves plus the '.iff' suffix.

   @{b}OVERWRITEREQ@{ub}
   Indicates you want an overwrite requester to appear if you try to save a
   picture file already existing.

   @{b}DESTPATH=<path>@{ub}
   Specifies the default name of the path in which you want to save the
   screens.


@Endnode
@Node "CLI" "CLI arguments"

@{b}@{u}CLI arguments@{uu}@{ub}

ScreenToIFF recognizes the following CLI arguments:

   @{b}XPOS <n>@{ub}
   Specifies the @{"main window" link "MAW"}'s horizontal position.

   @{b}YPOS <n>@{ub}
   Specifies the @{"main window" link "MAW"}'s vertical position.

   @{b}PUBLIC@{ub}
   Indicates you want to handle public screens only.

   @{b}ASKFILENAME@{ub}
   Indicates you want a file requester to appear when saving the screens,
   otherwise, the program will save the screens in the directory specified by
   'DESTPATH' with the name of the screens themselves plus the '.iff' suffix.

   @{b}OVERWRITEREQ@{ub}
   Indicates you want an overwrite requester to appear if you try to save a
   picture file already existing.

   @{b}DESTPATH <path>@{ub}
   Specifies the default name of the path in which you want to save the
   screens.

   @{b}PUBSCREEN <name>@{ub}
   Specifies the name of the public screen you want to save without opening
   the user interface. The program will save the screen in the directory
   specified by 'DESTPATH' with the name of the screen itself plus the '.iff'
   suffix.

   @{b}ALL@{ub}
   Indicates you want to save all the open screens without opening the user
   interface. The program will save the screens in the directory specified by
   'DESTPATH' with the name of the screens themselves plus the '.iff' suffix.

   @{b}LIST <file>@{ub}
   Indicates you want to save the list of open screens as a text file. The
   program will save the list with the name <file> without opening the user
   interface.


@Endnode
@Node "MAW" "The main window"

@{b}@{u}The main window@{uu}@{ub}

After you start the program, the main window containing the list of the
current open screens appears. To save a screen, double-click on its name, or
select the name and click on the 'Save' button. The main window disappears and
a file requester pops up. Select a file to save as and click on the 'Ok'
button. After the screen has been saved, the main window appears again. Click
on the 'Quit' button to quit the program.


@Endnode
@Node "MEN" "The menus"

@{b}@{u}The menus@{uu}@{ub}

ScreenToIFF provides the following menus:

   @{b}Project/Save@{ub}
   Saves the selected screen.

   @{b}Project/Save all@{ub}
   Saves all the open screens.

   @{b}Project/Save list@{ub}
   Saves the list of open screens as a text file.

   @{b}Project/Update@{ub}
   Updates the list of open screens.

   @{b}Project/Iconify@{ub}
   Iconifies the program.

   @{b}Project/About...@{ub}
   Shows some information about the program.

   @{b}Project/Quit@{ub}
   Quits the program.



   @{b}Options/Public screens@{ub}
   Indicates you want to handle public screens only.

   @{b}Options/Ask file name@{ub}
   Indicates you want a file requester to appear when saving the screens,
   otherwise, the program will save the screens in the directory specified by
   the 'DESTPATH' @{"ToolType" link "TOO"} or @{"CLI argument" link "CLI"} with the name of the
   screens themselves plus the '.iff' suffix.

   @{b}Options/Overwrite requester@{ub}
   Indicates you want an overwrite requester to appear if you try to save a
   picture file already existing.


@Endnode
@Node "NOT" "Notes"

@{b}@{u}Notes@{uu}@{ub}

   - The program sets the 'SCREENTOIFF_RC' environment variable when
     quitting. It contains the error level of the last operation (0=success,
     5=warn, 20=fail).


@Endnode
@Node "GUA" "Guarantee"

@{b}@{u}Guarantee@{uu}@{ub}

The program has been tested several times, but its reliability is not
guaranteed at 100%. I (@{"the author" link "AUT"}) do not consider myself responsible
for loss or damage of data as consequence of the use of the program. Use
ScreenToIFF at your own risk.


@Endnode
