@Node "HIS" "History"

@{b}@{u}History@{uu}@{ub}

   1.0  - First release.

   1.01 - Odd width screens were not saved correctly.
        - Now the program do not automatically quit after a screen has been
          saved.
        - Some other minor changes.

   1.1  - Added the 'XPOS', 'YPOS' and 'SAVEPATH' @{"ToolTypes" link "TOO"} and
          @{"CLI arguments" link "CLI"}.
        - Now you can save a screen with a simple double-click.
        - Added the 'Project' @{"menu" link "MEN"} containing the 'Update', 'Iconify',
          'About...' and 'Quit' items.
        - Some other minor changes.

   1.2  - The program locked if you iconified it and its icon could not be
          found.
        - Renamed the 'SAVEPATH' @{"ToolType" link "TOO"} and @{"CLI argument" link "CLI"} as
          'DESTPATH'.
        - Now the program uses the dos.library ReadArgs() function to read
          the @{"CLI arguments" link "CLI"}.
        - Added the 'PUBLIC', 'ASKFILENAME' and 'OVERWRITEREQ'
          @{"ToolTypes" link "TOO"} and @{"CLI arguments" link "CLI"}.
        - Added the 'PUBSCREEN', 'ALL' and 'LIST' @{"CLI arguments" link "CLI"}.
        - Added the 'Save', 'Save all' and 'Save list' items to the 'Project'
          @{"menu" link "MEN"}.
        - Added the 'Options' @{"menu" link "MEN"} containing the 'Public screens',
          'Ask file name' and 'Overwrite requester' items.
        - Now the program returns an error code by setting the
          'SCREENTOIFF_RC' environment variable.
        - Some other minor changes.

   1.21 - The program did not work on 68000/68010 machines.
        - Another minor change.

   1.22 - Very wide screens were not saved correctly.
        - If a patch like VisualPrefs or UrouHack was running, there were
          problems when iconifying or quitting the program.
        - Now the @{"ToolTypes" link "TOO"} are read even if you change the program's
          name.
        - Some other minor changes.


@Endnode
